[We posted news of a leishmaniasis outbreak in Tarija Department on 30 Jan 2022 (see archive 20220130.8701160) and assumed it was cutaneous leishmaniasis. However, it now seems that it is visceral leishmaniasis.

In the 2012 review of the worldwide incidence of leishmaniasis (Alvar J, et al. Leishmaniasis worldwide and global estimates of its incidence. PLoS One. 2012;7(5):e35671; https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0035671) annex 10, Bolivia), visceral leishmaniasis was, at the time of the review, not found in the Tarija region. Bolivia has the highest rate of cutaneous leishmaniasis in South America (Ballart C, et al. Clinical and immunological characteristics of tegumentary leishmaniasis cases in Bolivia. PLoS Negl Trop Dis. 2021; 15(3): e0009223; <https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pntd.0009223). - Mod.EP

